0                                   8097              *
                                    8098              *  Release the Wings work area (if the heap hasn't
                                    8099              *  changed on us in the meantime).
                                    8100              *
                                    8101              *  On entry:
                                    8102              *    CPDEVP - Points to the work area to be released.
                                    8103              *
                                    8104              *  ON EXIT:
                                    8105              *     If the heap hasn't changed, the work area will be
                                    8106              *     released and CPDEVP will be cleared. Otherwise,
                                    8107              *     the work area will not be freed (because we can't
                                    8108              *     shrink the heap).
                                    8109              *
                                    8110              *
 0000C8 50E0 D000/9008_      00000  8111              RLSWA    PROC  ,
 USING  *,R7
 0000E2 5850 BE58            00E58  8150                       L     R5,CPDEVP
 USING  WGSWA,R5                    8151                       WITH  (WGSWA,R5),BEGIN
 0000E6 58E0 7036/0DEE       00118  8165  1                      VCALL MARKHEAP            Get current heap ptr
 0000EC 59F0 5004/4770_      00004  8169  1                      IF    (R15,EQ,WGSNHEAP),BEGIN  We can reduce the heap...
 0000F4 58F0 5000            00000  8186  2                        L     R15,WGSOHEAP
 0000F8 58E0 703A/0DEE       0011C  8187  2                        VCALL RELHEAP             Release WGSWA
 0000FE D703 BE58 BE58 00E58 00E58  8191  2                        CLEAR CPDEVP
 000104                             8198  1                      END
 DROP   WGSWA,R5                    8202                       END
 000104 18D8/9808 D004_             8210                       PEND  ,
 DROP   *,R7

0                                   8245              *
                                    8246              *
                                    8247              *  WGSOPEN - WINGS OPEN
                                    8248              *
                                    8249              *  ON ENTRY:
                                    8250              *  FFINFO DSECT CONTAINS FILE NAME/FORMAT/OPTIONS AND
                                    8251              *  FILE SYSTEM INFORMATION.
                                    8252              *
                                    8253              *  ON EXIT:
                                    8254              *  R15=0, ALL OK
                                    8255              *  R15=NZ, CPERRID CONTAINS ERROR, MSG TSEG'D
                                    8256              *
                                    8257              *  CAUTION!:
                                    8258              *  SOME SCANNING ERRORS EXIT VIA CVERROR
                                    8259              *  (THIS COULD BE CHANGED AND FIXED.)
                                    8260              *
                                    8261              *  THIS ROUTINE MUST PROCESS FILE NAME AND OPTIONS.
                                    8262              *  THIS ROUTINE MUST GATHER INFO REQUIRED TO OPEN FILE.
                                    8263              *  THIS ROUTINE MUST OPEN A PATH TO WINGS FILE SERVER.
                                    8264              *  THIS ROUTINE MUST START UP WINGS SERVER PROTOCOL.
                                    8265              *  THIS ROUTINE MUST PROCESS FILE SERVER RETURNS.
                                    8266              *
                                    8267              *  NOTE:
                                    8268              *  MOST OPTIONS ARE PROCESSED BY SEG'ING THEM INTO THE WINGS
                                    8269              *  WRITE BUFFER.   THE BUFFER IS NOT (MUST NOT BE!) WRITTEN
                                    8270              *  TO WINGS UNTIL THE PATH IS OPENED.  WE DO NOT OPEN THE
                                    8271              *  PATH FIRST BECAUSE WE WANT TO CATCH ANY SYNTAX OR OPTION
                                    8272              *  ERRORS BEFORE WE GO TO THE OVERHEAD OF OPENING THE PATH.
                                    8273              *
                                    8274              *  CAUTION!!
                                    8275              *  FILE SYSTEM OPTIONS MAY BE SAME AS FILE OPTIONS. (EG. VOLUME=
                                    8276              *  MAY BE SPECIFIED TWICE.)  WE PROCESS THE FILE SYSTEM FIRST
                                    8277              *  AND THE SPECIFIC FILE OPTIONS NEXT.  THUS, IF THERE ARE
                                    8278              *  DUPLICATE OPTIONS, THE SECOND OCCURANCE SHOULD OVERRIDE THE
                                    8279              *  FIRST.  WINGS SERVER BEWARE !
                                    8280              *
                                    8281              *
 000120 50E0 D000/9008_      00000  8282              WGSOPEN  XPROC ,
 USING  *,R7
 00013A 5860 BE54            00E54  8322                       L     R6,CPFINFOP
 USING  FFINFO,R6                   8323                       USING FFINFO,R6

0                                  14444              *
                                   14445              *  PGAPPEND - Append indicated line to current Page A
                                   14446              *
                                   14447              *  This routine is used by the various SHOW routines to
                                   14448              *  append the indicated display line coming back from the
                                   14449              *  Wings server to the current page in the Page A register.
                                   14450              *
                                   14451              *  On entry:
                                   14452              *     R1,R0 hold the location and length of the line
                                   14453              *     PAR   points to the page
                                   14454              *
                                   14455              *     Note: Since a 0 length line cannot be stored on
                                   14456              *           the page, this routine will store a line
                                   14457              *           consisting of 1 blank if R0 is 0 on input.
                                   14458              *
                                   14459              *
                                   14460              *  On exit:
                                   14461              *     R15=0 Line appended successfully
                                   14462              *     R15=NZ Not enough space on page
                                   14463              *
 001ABA 50E0 D000/9008_      00000 14464              PGAPPEND PROC ,
 USING  *,R7
 001AD4 9001 D000/41D0_      00000 14503                       XPUSH R0,R1
 001ADC 1200/4770 7016             14506                       IF    (R0,Z),BEGIN
 001AE2 4100 0001            00001 14520  1                      LA    R0,1
 001AE6 4110 C4D8            004D8 14521  1                      LA    R1,CVBLANKS
 001AEA                            14522                       END
 001AEA 4830 9000            00000 14526                       LH    R3,@PAR             Get count on page now
 001AEE 1A30                       14527                       AR    R3,R0
 001AF0 5930 707C            01B50 14528                       C     R3,=A(CVPSZ-3)      That's how much there is
 001AF4 4730 705C            01B30 14529                       IF    LE,BEGIN
 001AF8 4830 9000            00000 14540  1                      LH    R3,@PAR             Amount currently on page
 001AFC 4129 3001            00001 14541  1                      LA    R2,@R3+1(PAR)       Convert offset to address
 001B00 1A30                       14542  1                      AR    R3,R0
 001B02 4130 3001            00001 14543  1                      LA    R3,@R3+1            Store the new count
 001B06 4030 9000            00000 14544  1                      STH   R3,@PAR
 001B0A 1830                       14545  1                      LR    R3,R0
 001B0C 1200/47D0 7044             14546  1                      IF    (R0,P),BEGIN
 001B12 0630/4430 7086_            14560  2                        DEX   R3,'MVC @R2+1(0),@R1'  Move the message in
 001B18                            14579  1                      END
 001B18 4130 3001            00001 14583  1                      LA    R3,@R3+1            Prefix message with
 001B1C 4230 2000            00000 14584  1                      STC   R3,@R2                 a count field.
 001B20 4132 3001            00001 14585  1                      LA    R3,@R3+1(R2)
 001B24 9200 3000      00000       14586  1                      MVI   @R3,0               Store an end flag
 001B28 58E0 7080/0DEE       01B54 14587  1                      PMARK PAR                  and mark the page as changed
 001B2E 1BFF                       14592  1                      CLEAR R15                 All ok
 001B30                            14596                       END
 001B30 7060/47F0 7064 01B30 01AF6 14600                       ELSE  BEGIN
 001B34 41F0 0004            00004 14611  1                      LA    R15,4               Insufficient space
 001B38                            14612                       END
 001B38 4BD0 7084/9801_      01B58 14616                       XPOP  R0,R1
 001B40 18D8/9808 D004_            14619                       PEND ,
 DROP   *,R7
                                   14639                       QLTORG

0                                  14655              *
                                   14656              *  PGRELS   - Release all pages in a page array
                                   14657              *
                                   14658              *  This routine is called to release all the pages in an array
                                   14659              *  of pages. It's called by the SHOW commands.
                                   14660              *
                                   14661              *  On entry:
                                   14662              *   R0 - Contains the number of items in the array
                                   14663              *   R1 - Points to the array of page identifiers
                                   14664              *
                                   14665              *  On output:
                                   14666              *   Pages released.
                                   14667              *

 001B92 5821 5000            00000 14746  2                        L     R2,0(R1,R5)
 001B96 1802/58E0 7046_            14747  2                        PGET  PAR,(R2)
 001B9E 58E0 704A/0DEE       01BC4 14756  2                        PFREE PAR,EMPTY
 001BA4 4130 3001            00001 14762  2                        LA    R3,1(,R3)
 001BA8 47F0 700C            01B86 14763  1                      END

                                   16760              *  WGSHODSN - WINGS SHOW DSNAMES
                                   16761              *
                                   16762              *  ON ENTRY:
                                   16763              *  FFINFO DSECT CONTAINS FILE NAME/OPTIONS AND
                                   16764              *  FILE SYSTEM INFORMATION.
                                   16765              *  R1  Point to show dsnames  argument and
                                   16766              *      return block.
                                   16767              *
                                   16768              *  ON EXIT:
                                   16769              *  R15=0, ALL OK
                                   16770              *  R15=4 CPERRID CONTAINS ERROR, MSG TSEG'D
                                   16771              *  R15 = 8 ALL OK, BUT WE RAN OUT OF PAGES TO HOLD

0                                  18571              *
                                   18572              * This routine determines whether or not the indicated catalog

                                   18574              * in the SHOW CAT arguments.

                                   18576              * Inputs:

                                   18582              *  R0,R1 - Same as on input

                                   18585              *

0                                  18909              *
                                   18910              *  WGSHOCAT - WINGS SHOW CATALOG
                                   18911              *
                                   18912              *  ON ENTRY:
                                   18913              *  FFINFO DSECT CONTAINS FILE NAME/OPTIONS AND
                                   18914              *  FILE SYSTEM INFORMATION.
                                   18915              *  R1  Point to show catalog argument and
                                   18916              *      return block.
                                   18917              *
                                   18918              *  ON EXIT:
                                   18919              *  R15=0, ALL OK
                                   18920              *  R15=4 CPERRID CONTAINS ERROR, MSG TSEG'D
                                   18921              *  R15 = 8 ALL OK, BUT WE RAN OUT OF PAGES TO HOLD

                                   19273              *   Remove performance change. We have to ask for volume information

                                   19276              *   the dataset is on disk, and is a standard WYLBUR dsname. Thus,
                                   19277              *   we need the information about the device type.

0                                  30740              *
                                   30741              *  CVOLHACK - CURRENT VOLUME HACK
                                   30742              *
                                   30743              *  IF WE HAD 'USE X ON SYSXXX' FOLLOWED BY A
                                   30744              *  'SAVE *' OR A 'USE *' ETC.  WE MUST USE THE
                                   30745              *  PREFIX VOLUME SYSXXX.  THAT IS WHAT THIS HACK
                                   30746              *  DOES.
                                   30747              *
                                   30748              *  APPLY HACK IF, 1. NAME IS *, 2. NO VOLUME IS SPECIFIED,
                                   30749              *  AND 3. IF PREFIX VOLUME EXISTS.
                                   30750              *
                                   30751              *  HACK IS TO MOVE PREFIX VOLUME IN AS A SPECIFIED VOLUME.
                                   30752              *  UGG.  EFFECTIVE THOUGH.
                                   30753              *
                                   30754              *  YUCK2,,, THIS ROUTINE MAY EXIT DIRECTLY IF PROMPT IS
                                   30755              *  NOT ANSWERED PROPERLY FOR 'SAV XXX#*', VERY UNUSUAL CASE
                                   30756              *  BUT STILL A YUCK2
                                   30757              *

                                   31058              *  WGSREAD - WINGS READ
                                   31059              *
                                   31060              *  ON ENTRY:
                                   31061              *    R1,R0 - BUFFER LOC,LEN TO READ LINE INTO
                                   31062              *
                                   31063              *  ON EXIT:

0                                  31461              *
                                   31462              *
                                   31463              *  WGSWRITE - WINGS WRITE ROUTINE
                                   31464              *
                                   31465              *  WE USE SEG WRITE TO WRITE TO WINGS OUTPUT BUFFER.
                                   31466              *
                                   31467              *  ON ENTRY:
                                   31468              *    R1,R0 - LINE TO WRITE
                                   31469              *    R2 - LINE NUMBER TO WRITE
                                   31470              *
                                   31471              *  ON EXIT:
                                   31472              *    IF ERROR, WE EXIT DIRECTLY
                                   31473              *
                                   31474              *  NOTE:
                                   31475              *  THIS ROUTINE WRITES ONLY LINES (IE. FILE TEXT).
                                   31476              *  TO WRITE STRAIGHT WINGS STUFF, YOU CAN SEG IT
                                   31477              *  TO THE WINGS BUFFER. OR DIRECTLY WRITE IT IF
                                   31478              *  YOU CALL WPWRITE (WINGS PATH WRITE). IF YOU WRITE
                                   31479              *  DIRECTLY, THE BUFFER STUFF IS BYPASSED AND MAY BE
                                   31480              *  OUT OF ORDER.
                                   31481              *
                                   31482              *  NOTE:
                                   31483              *  EACH LINE IS WRITTEN TO WINGS AS 4 BYTES TOTAL LENGTH,
                                   31484              *  8 BYTES LINE NUMBER IN CHAR FORMAT, N BYTES TEXT.
                                   31485              *
 000000                00000 001E6 31486              WGSWWA   RECORD BEGIN
 000000                            31494  1           WGSWLLEN   DS    F
                                   31495  1           WGSWLINE   DS    XL(2*&LINESZ+12)
 000004                                   1          +WGSWLINE   DS    XL(2*235+12)
 0001E6                001E6 001E6 31496                       END

                                   31506              *

0                                  33417              *
                                   33418              *
                                   33419              *  WWFORMAT - WINGS WRITE LINE FORMAT ROUTINE
                                   33420              *
                                   33421              *  THIS ROUTINE DOES ANY INTEGER, NUMBERED, LRECL PROCESSING
                                   33422              *
                                   33423              *  ON ENTRY:
                                   33424              *    R1,R0 - LINE LOCATION LENGTH

0                                  36688              *
                                   36689              *  WRDERROR
                                   36690              *
                                   36691              *  GET ERRID AND ERROR MSG FROM PATH ERROR PACKET
                                   36692              *
                                   36693              *  ON ENTRY:
                                   36694              *    R1,R0 - ERROR PACKET LOCATION LENGTH
                                   36695              *
                                   36696              *  ON EXIT:
                                   36697              *    CPERRID SET.  ERROR MESSAGE IS TSEG'ED
                                   36698              *    R15 SET TO ZERO.
                                   36699              *
                                   36700              *  NOTE:
                                   36701              *  ANYTHING THAT IS NOT RECOGNIZED IS IGNORED.
                                   36702              *
                                   36703              *  NOTE:
                                   36704              *  WE PROCESS LIBFULL CONDENSE ERROR HERE.  IT
                                   36705              *  WOULD BE BEST IF THIS WAS PROCESSED IN HIGHER
                                   36706              *  LEVEL ROUTINE, (EG. SAVE ROUTINE),  BUT WE
                                   36707              *  MAY GET ERROR RETURN DURING WRITE, AND
                                   36708              *  AS OF NOW WYLBUR DOES NOT RETURN ERRORS ON
                                   36709              *  WRITE.  SO WE DO IT HERE.
                                   36710              *
                                   36711              *

0                                  38951              *
                                   38952              *  WPSEGERR - PROCESS WINGS PATH SEG WRITE ERROR
                                   38953              *
                                   38954              *  WE GOT AN ERROR WHILE TRYING TO WRITE A WINGS
                                   38955              *  FILE.   WE TRY TO  READ A 'FILE_ERROR:' FROM
                                   38956              *  OUR PARTNER TO SEE WHAT THE ERROR IS.
                                   38957              *
                                   38958              *  IF ERROR IS 'LIBFULL' WE ASK TO CONDENSE.
                                   38959              *  IF ERROR IS '....' (NO OTHERS YET)
                                   38960              *  IF WE GET UNRECOGNIZED 'FILE_ERROR:' WE SEND
                                   38961              *     ERROR ID, ERROR MSG BACK TO USER
                                   38962              *  IF WE GET ERROR TRYING TO READ FROM PARTNER,
                                   38963              *     WE GIVE UP WITH GENERIC
                                   38964              *
                                   38965              *  FINALLY WE CLOSE FILE
                                   38966              *
                                   38967              *
 000000                00000 00200 38968              WSEWA    RECORD BEGIN
 000000                            38976  1           WSEBUF     DS    CL512
 000200                00200 00200 38977                       END
                                   38986              *
                                   38987              *
 007B7A 50E0 D000/9008_      00000 38988              WPSEGERR PROC  WSEWA

0                                  41243              *
                                   41244              *
                                   41245              *   RETLIBMB - RETURN FILE NAME IN LIB#MEMBER FORMAT
                                   41246              *
                                   41247              *
                                   41248              *   ON ENTRY:
                                   41249              *      R1,R0 - FILE NAME LOC, LEN
                                   41250              *      R2 - LOCATION TO PUT NAME
                                   41251              *
                                   41252              *   ON EXIT:
                                   41253              *      R1,R0 - FILE NAME (LIB#MEM) LOC, LEN
                                   41254              *              (R1=R2 ON EXIT; R0 IS ACTUAL LEN)
                                   41255              *
                                   41256              *   NOTE:
                                   41257              *     IF NO MEMBER, FILE NAME IS RETURNED AS EXPECTED
                                   41258              *
                                   41259              *   NOTE:
                                   41260              *     IF NOT TYPE WINGS/OLDIBM WE SHOULD NOT
                                   41261              *     RETURN MEMBER. '(' OR ')' MAY BE PART OF THE FILE
                                   41262              *     NAME.   WHAT DO YOU SAY !
                                   41263              *
                                   41264              *   NOTES, CAUTION!
                                   41265              *     RETURN AREA (@R2) SHOULD BE BIG ENOUGH TO HOLD
                                   41266              *     MAX FILE NAME (CURRENTLY 128 BYTES).  ON EXIT
                                   41267              *     R1 = R2.
                                   41268              *
                                   41269              *

0                                  42664              
                                   42665                                                                                   
                                   42666                BUILDDSN -- Routine to build the OS file name given the name       
                                   42667                  and all the other pieces.                                        
                                   42668                                                                                   
                                   42669                  On entry:                                                        
                                   42670                     R1  - FILPB ptr                                               
                                   42671                     R2  - Pointer to store ERRID                                  
                                   42672                     R15 - Error message SEGCB ptr                                 
                                   42673                                                                                   
                                   42674                  On exit, R15 (and cc):                                           
                                   42675                     0 = ok; DSNAME and MEMBER filled in:                          
                                   42676                           FILPBDSNAME - 44 character OS file name                 
                                   42677                           FILPBDSMEM  - 8 character member name                   
                                   42678                                           (binary zero if none)                   
                                   42679                           FILPBDSACCT - account (uuugg) of dsname owner           
                                   42680                                           (binary zero if non-standard ds)        
                                   42681                                                                                   
                                   42682                     nz= error, R1,R0 = error message loc, len, ERRID stored       
                                   42683                                                                                   
                                                      
0000000                00000 000CC 42684              BDSNWA   RECORD BEGIN
 000000                            42692  1           BDSNERAD   DS    A                   ERRID ptr
 000004                            42693  1           BDSNESGP   DS    A                   Error SEGCB ptr
 000008                            42694  1           BDSNERID   DS    CL8                 ERRID save
                                   42695  1           BDSNSG     SEGCB ,                   Filname expansion SEGCB
 000010 00                         42696  1 01-SEGCB +$$$SEGCB1074   DS 0F
 BDSNSGCOD.BDSNSGS 01 EQ
 BDSNSGCOD.BDSNSGW 02 EQ

0                                  46910              
                                   46911                                                                                   
                                   46912                CHECKDSN -- Routine to check that the file name conforms           
                                   46913                  to the OS data set name conventions.                             
                                   46914                                                                                   
                                   46915                    On entry:                                                      
                                   46916                      R1  - FILPB ptr                                              
                                   46917                      R15 - Error message SEGCB ptr                                
                                   46918                                                                                   
                                   46919                    On exit, R15 (and CC):                                         
                                   46920                      0 = ok                                                       
                                   46921                      nz= error, R1,R0 = error message loc, len                    
                                   46922                                                                                   
                                                      
0000000                00000 00008 46923              CDSNWA   RECORD BEGIN
 000000                            46931  1           CDSNESGP   DS    A                   Error SEGCB ptr
 000004                            46932  1           CDSNTYPE   DS    F                   Max TRT value for valid dsn chars
 000008                00008 00008 46933                       END
                                   46942
